<sections.4>
Conclusions
irst, the novel homozygous truncating mutation in the isoform-1 specific region of the  -terminus can lead not only to a severe early-onset form of , woolly hair and an acantholytic form of palmoplantar keratoderma, but also to features of non-compaction. econd, this cardiomyopathy can occur in hearts with normally structured intercalated discs and desmin networks.Conclusions
First, the novel homozygous truncating mutation in the isoform-1 specific region of the DSP C-terminus can lead not only to a severe early-onset form of DCM, woolly hair and an acantholytic form of palmoplantar keratoderma, but also to features of non-compaction. Second, this cardiomyopathy can occur in hearts with normally structured intercalated discs and desmin networks.
